    <h1><span>Selected Cellular Automata Links</span></h1>

    <h2><span>Game of Life</span></h2>

    <ul>
      <li><span><a href="http://www.radicaleye.com/lifepage/">Paul
      Callahan's Life page</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://alife.santafe.edu/~joke/rsc/ships_toc.html">
      Spaceships in Conway's game of Life</a>, <a href= 
      "http://www.tip.net.au/~dbell/">David Bell</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.argentum.freeserve.co.uk/ships.zip">Life
      spaceship collection</a>, <a href= 
      "http://www.argentum.freeserve.co.uk/life.htm">Stephen
      Silver</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.math.ucdavis.edu/~dean/RLE/corder.html">Corderman
      spaceships and puffers</a>, <a href= 
      "http://www.math.ucdavis.edu/~dean/life.html">Dean
      Hickerson</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://home.interserv.com/~mniemiec/lifepage.htm">Mark
      Niemiec's catalog</a> of small objects and their syntheses
      from gliders.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.pentadecathlon.com/LifeInfo/Objects/Class3/Moving.html">
      Moving objects</a> catalogued by period and number of live
      cells, <a href= 
      "http://www.pentadecathlon.com/LifeInfo/LifeInfo.html">
      Heinrich Koenig</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://paradise.caltech.edu/~cook/Workshop/CAs/2DOutTot/Life/StillLife/StillLifeTheory.html">
      Still life theory</a>, <a href= 
      "http://paradise.caltech.edu/~cook/">Matthew Cook</a> (see
      also his <a href= 
      "http://www.msri.org/publications/ln/msri/2000/gametheory/cook/1/index.html">
      presentation at the MSRI combinatorial game theory research
      workshop</a>).</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://entropymine.com/jason/life/status.html">Game of Life
      Status Page</a>, <a href=
      "http://entropymine.com/jason/life/">Jason
      Summers</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://acf5.nyu.edu/~mm64/x52.9264/october1970.html">Martin
      Gardner's Scientific American column</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://tomas.rokicki.com/mcc/">
      Metacatacryst</a>. Tomas Rokicki uses a <a href= 
      "http://tomas.rokicki.com/hlife/">hashlife</a> algorithm to
      simulate a quadratic-growth pattern to ridiculous numbers of
      generations.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://dmoz.org/Computers/Artificial_Life/Cellular_Automata/Conway's_Game_Of_Life/">
      Open Directory: Conway's Game of Life</a>.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.rennard.org/alife/english/logicellgb.html">
      LogiCell</a> implementation of Boolean logic in Conway's
      Life.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span>Spaceships in other cellular automata</span></h2>

    <ul>
      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://groups.google.com/groups?threadm=1052774743.21828@itz.pp.sci.fi">
      Gliders in 4-neighbor semitotalistic 2D cellular
      automata</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://finitenature.com/soliton_essay/">
      Finite nature: solitons</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://groups.google.com/groups?ic=1&amp;th=9e15384ba0ddf679,9">
      Rotations IV</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://web.syr.edu/~rsholmes/games/cell_aut/spaceship_survey.html">
      Rich Holmes' survey of small spaceships in various CA
      rules</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.math.ucdavis.edu/~dean/RLE/slowships.html">Slow
      alien spaceships</a>, <a href= 
      "http://www.math.ucdavis.edu/~dean/life.html">Dean
      Hickerson</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://entropymine.com/jason/life/alt/">
      Patterns for other Life-like rules</a>, <a href= 
      "http://entropymine.com/jason/life/">Jason
      Summers</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://www.frii.com/~dboll/lifevar.txt">
      Dave Boll's investigations of variant life
      rules</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href=
      "http://www.csun.edu/~kme52026/thesis.html">Kellie Evans'
      Ph.D. thesis</a> on variant life rules.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://hensel.lifepatterns.net/justfriends.html">Just
      Friends</a> non-totalistic rule with many interesting
      patterns.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.collidoscope.com/cgolve/rule32ab3.html">Rule
      3/2ab3</a>, another non-totalistic rule with small
      gliders.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://www.logic-ca.com/">The Logic
      Rule</a>, yet another non-totalistic rule with small photons
      and a nice replicator-based photon gun, allowing logic
      circuits to be built from glider streams.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.cse.sc.edu/~bays/trilife3/home.html">Triangular
      cellular automata</a>, Carter Bays. His rules 2,4/4,6 and
      2,4,6/4,6, at least, can generate gliders from random initial
      conditions.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.keithwiley.com/artificialLife/strangeUniverse.shtml">Strange
      Universe</a>, gliders in a 12-neighbor triangular
      CA.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.bayarea.net/~maydwell/htdoc/ca/hexgallery.html">
      Hexagonal CA gallery</a>, showing several hexagonal rules
      with gliders.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://www.hexatron.com/hexca/index.html">
      Hexatron</a>. More hexagonal rules with gliders.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://delta.cs.cinvestav.mx/~mcintosh/comun/RULE110W/RULE110.html">
      Gliders in rule 110</a>, a one-dimensional CA recently proven
      Turing-complete by Matthew Cook.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~ken/solitons.html">Solitons and
      particles in cellular automata: a
      bibliography</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.cs.sc.edu/~huggins/meeker/Life_4D/objects.html">
      Some 3d and 4d Game of Life objects</a></span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2><span>General references</span></h2>

    <ul>
      <li><span><a href="http://psoup.math.wisc.edu/kitchen.html">
      David Griffeath's primordial soup kitchen</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://alife.santafe.edu/alife/topics/cas/ca-faq/ca-faq.html">
      Frequently asked questions about cellular
      automata</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://penguin.phy.bnl.gov/www/xtoys/gallery/gallery.html">
      Xtoys Gallery</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.santafe.edu/~wuensch/cplex_ab.html">Classifying
      cellular automata automatically</a>, Andrew
      Wuensche.</span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.mirwoj.opus.chelm.pl/ca/ca_files_formats.html">
      Cellular automaton file formats</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href= 
      "http://www.rennard.org/alife/english/acintrogb01.html">
      Introduction to cellular automata</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href=
      "http://www.geocities.com/robisais/3dca.html">3d cellular
      automata links</a></span></li>

      <li><span><a href="http://cell-auto.com/optimisation/">
      Cellular Automata - Optimisation</a>. Interesting discussion
      of CA programming techniques.</span></li>
    </ul>
